  "prompt": "What are Hazel eyes?",
  "response": "Hazel eyes are characterized by a combination of colors, typically including shades of brown, green, and amber. The unique appearance of hazel eyes can vary widely, as they may appear to shift in color depending on lighting conditions and the colors they are paired with in clothing or surroundings. \n\nHazel eyes often exhibit a central brown area surrounded by green or gold flecks, creating a multicolored effect. This coloration is due to the presence of varying amounts of melanin and the way light is refracted through the iris. Because hazel eyes encompass a range of shades and tones, they can appear quite different from person to person, contributing to their distinctive and striking appearance.",
